<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>

  <!--
    Better Traders Guild - Cleansweeper Mech Clean Duty

    BTG_MechClean: room-bound janitor behaviour for the Cleansweeper mech. Cleaning is
    confined strictly to the one layout room the mech was spawned into (see CleanArea) -
    its lord's room, matched def-agnostically and by rect membership, so a room composed
    of several rects works exactly. The mech never scans, reserves, or paths to filth in
    any other room or outside the walls; that room is its private "home area".

    Priority order:
    1. Clean - sweep the nearest in-range reachable filth and the cluster around it in a
       single BTG_Clean job (vanilla Clean minus the player Home-area gate, which a TG
       settlement never satisfies; see JobDriver_BTGCleanFilth), nearest-first queue,
       then re-evaluate.
    2. Idle - when no qualifying filth remains, walk back to near the anchor point and go
       dormant (SelfShutdown, forceSleep off so the job's expiry re-checks for filth and
       wakes it within ~250 ticks).

    Used by: LordJob_MechClean, assigned via RoomMechLordHelper to the Cleansweeper mech
    (RoomPart Mech_Cleansweeper, behavior=Clean).
  -->

  <DutyDef>
    <defName>BTG_MechClean</defName>
    <thinkNode Class="ThinkNode_Priority">
      <subNodes>
        <!-- 1. Clean nearby in-bounds filth, nearest-first, a cluster per job. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.Mechs.JobGiver_BTGMechCleanFilth" />
        <!-- 2. Idle: return home and dormant self-charge; re-checks for filth on expiry. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.Mechs.JobGiver_BTGMechCleanStandby" />
      </subNodes>
    </thinkNode>
  </DutyDef>

</Defs>
